<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="658" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[789,1382,273,700]" pageId="39" pageNumber="658">
<taxonomicName box="[792,899,273,306]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Otomops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="658" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Otomops</taxonomicName>
harrisoni was until recently included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1897" box="[940,1140,317,346]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Otomops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="658" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="martiensseni">O. martiensseni</taxonomicName>
but the two species can be distinguished on molecular, ecological, biogeographic and morphometric grounds. A recent molecular study by B. D. Patterson and colleagues, in 2018, showed that the two species maintain their genetic distinctness where they co-occur (
<collectingCountry box="[802,916,589,622]" name="Uganda" pageId="39" pageNumber="658">Uganda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[937,1024,589,622]" name="Kenya" pageId="39" pageNumber="658">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1113,1230,589,622]" name="Rwanda" pageId="39" pageNumber="658">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
), reinforcing the conclusion that they are valid species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="658" type="distribution">
